\rho_{\Lambda}^{\mathrm{eff}} = m_{\Phi}^{2} M_{P}^{2} \beta_{0}.
\end{equation}
This corresponds to an effective cosmological constant:
\begin{equation}
\Lambda_{\mathrm{eff}} = m_{\Phi}^{2} \beta_{0}.
\end{equation}
Unlike standard $\Lambda$CDM, this term is screened at $r < 1/m_{\Phi}$ via the Vainshtein mechanism, but manifests fully at cosmological scales.

