\section{Conclusion}

We have reformulated the Energy-Space Equivalence framework using the mathematically robust dRGT massive gravity action. This resolves previous stability concerns by explicitly eliminating the Boulware-Deser ghost. The theory unifies geometry and energy by treating them as different regimes of a single massive tensor field. While challenges remain---specifically regarding the naturalness of the resonance frequencies---the framework offers a consistent toy model for exploring physics beyond the Standard Model and General Relativity.

