\section{Proof of Ghost-Freedom (Constraint Analysis)}
\label{app:constraints}

To demonstrate that the theory propagates 5 physical degrees of freedom rather than 6 (which would imply a ghost), we perform a Hamiltonian analysis using the ADM decomposition.

\subsection{Degree of Freedom Counting}
The reference metric $S_{\mu\nu}$ breaks the full diffeomorphism group down to a diagonal subgroup. The shift vector $N^{i}$ is no longer a Lagrange multiplier, but the lapse $N$ remains linear in the Hamiltonian. This preservation of linearity ensures the existence of a second-class constraint:

\begin{itemize}
    \item Phase space: 12 variables ($\gamma_{ij}$, $\pi^{ij}$)
    \item Primary constraint $\mathcal{C}$ from lapse linearity: 1
    \item Secondary constraint from $\dot{\mathcal{C}} \approx 0$: 1
\end{itemize}

These constraints form a second-class pair (non-vanishing Poisson bracket). Each second-class constraint removes one phase space degree of freedom:
\begin{equation}
\text{DoF} = \frac{1}{2}(12 - 2) = 5
\end{equation}
These correspond to the 5 polarization states of a massive spin-2 particle, confirming the absence of the Boulware-Deser ghost.

